            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>142</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by the monk lie and untruth (must be shunned). (With great censure he) is besmirched (here), and therefore, when he dies, ... afterwards [re]born in hell. [61d]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a8 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1949"/><citedRange>II, 32-34</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(empty) gossip, [but] he is [not stained] by it .... he is [re]born. And afterwards the Buddha spoke a strophe (concerning this in the assembly)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... without pride, advantage [and] right ... this one’s speech is after all. This strophe he spoke, (in order to make) the monk (turn) from evil.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>160</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[62d] The (Omniscient) was staying in the town (Vaiśā)lī .... a cup [set with] jewels, first to the Omniscient, then to the Satyaka; Sa(tyaka) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for [he is?] a lad. Each to their dear ... This you shall do, then I will enjoy this alms-bowl. Thereupon ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[63d] After the (reprimand) only Satyaka, the son of Ni(r)granthas, (gave) back (the cup).</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Mahā(kāśyapa) proclaimed to this assembly. A sinless (spoken word), this is always being praised [and] blameless</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>293</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... The word, that was spoken (in this way, that is well spoken). [64d] (If one speaks righteous, and not unrighteous), if one also speaks a friendly word, not an unfriendly one, if one also speaks the truth, [and] does not (tell a lie).</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is [a] word well spoken. (After this he spoke the three strophes:) The (well-)spoken word, that [is] the best, [thus] the noble ones speak of him.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>111</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (truth) one shall speak, not lie. [65d] (by which one) may neither torture (himself) nor hurt others.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ein solches Wort soll man sprechen, durch das man weder sich selbst quälen noch andere verletzen könnte. </seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Such a word one shall speak, by which one may neither torment oneself nor hurt others.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>314</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>111</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>39</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979d"/><citedRange>162</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The evil word spoken brings avarice ... (in this birth) as in the other it will not bring torture.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... it will have to be for the salvation. Law ... [66d] He spoke the third strophe: A friendly [word] one shall speak, a word which (is praised)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>133</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>756</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>168</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (These) three (strophes) he proclaimed for the avoidance of the evil word. The honoring word</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979d"/><citedRange>156</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>181</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [is] to lead from the land ... [is] good for both, for oneself [and] equally [so] for the others. Why do you not say the good (word?) [67d]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>270</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">and through that also the one, (who has gone from the) house ... the one standing in good discipline, not fear and anxiety for his life, not</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>178</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [His] own life that one will give [more readily], (nothing evil) this being will speak.</seg></seg></choice></p>
